                <h2>About Commercial Agriculture</h2>
                <p>Commercial agriculture is a large-scale farming system focused on producing crops and livestock for sale in markets, using modern technology and business principles to maximize efficiency and profitability.</p>

                <h3>Key Characteristics:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Large-scale production</li>
                    <li>High capital investment</li>
                    <li>Use of modern technology and machinery</li>
                    <li>Specialized crop cultivation</li>
                    <li>Market-oriented production</li>
                    <li>Economies of scale</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Common Practices:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Monoculture farming</li>
                    <li>Use of synthetic fertilizers and pesticides</li>
                    <li>Irrigation systems</li>
                    <li>Mechanized equipment</li>
                    <li>Global distribution networks</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
